        "contact": {
          "name": "Random User Generator",
          "url": "https://randomuser.me/"
        },
        "description": "A free, open-source API for generating random user data like names, emails, addresses, and more. Provides JSON, XML, CSV, or YAML objects. Like Lorem Ipsum, but for people.",
        "license": {
          "name": "Copyright Notice",
          "url": "https://randomuser.me/"
        },
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Production server",
            "url": "https://randomuser.me/api"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Random User Generator",
        "version": "1.4",
        "tagline": "Generate randomized fake user profiles for testing, prototyping, and demos",
        "homepage": "https://randomuser.me/",
        "docs_url": "https://randomuser.me/documentation",
        "license_short": "Free to use; profile photos sourced from UI Faces' authorized section (see UI Faces terms).",
        "license_md": "- Free to use for testing, prototyping, and development.\n- Profile photos are hand-picked from the authorized section of [UI Faces](https://uifaces.co/) — review their FAQ for photo usage terms.\n- No API key or authentication is required.\n- The service is community-maintained; check the project repository for the latest licence notes.",
        "about_md": "[Random User Generator](https://randomuser.me/) is a free service that returns realistic-looking but entirely fake user profiles. It is designed by Arron Hunt and developed by Keith Armstrong, with contributions from the open-source community.\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n- Personal info: name, gender, date of birth, age\n- Contact: email, phone, cell\n- Location: street, city, state, country, postcode, coordinates, timezone\n- Login credentials: username, password (plus salt, MD5/SHA1/SHA256 hashes), UUID\n- ID number, nationality, registration date\n- Profile pictures in thumbnail, medium, and large sizes\n\nRequests can be tuned via query parameters such as `results` (up to 5,000 per call), `gender`, `nat` (nationality filter, e.g. `us,dk,fr,gb`), `seed` (reproducible output), `inc`/`exc` (field selection), `page`, and `format` (JSON, XML, CSV, YAML, PrettyJSON). No authentication is required and CORS is enabled, so the API can be called directly from the browser. The base endpoint is `https://randomuser.me/api/`, with a pinned version available at `https://randomuser.me/api/1.4/`.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "get_random_user": "Fetches one or more randomly generated user profiles from `https://randomuser.me/api/`, with optional `results`, `gender`, `nat`, `seed`, `inc`, `exc`, `page`, and `format` query parameters."
        },
